Have you thought about uploading some of your videos to floatplane.com? You've already made the product and can create a new income stream with it. LTT, 5 US$ and up a month for 7-19 videos a week, loads some of their videos a little earlier than on YT, Forgotten Weapons, 3 US$ monthly for 6 a week, uploads to both at the same time, both ways seems to work well. They know you still need your YT going, there's no algorithm for promoting videos on FP.
It's be cool to see a foodie channel there.

snippet.textDisplay: I can't remember ever being so disappointed in a SORTED video.  Make these on Sunday, maybe, but not mid week.  On a Wednesday, I would have just seasoned everything and put it in the oven in order of cooking time.  They WAY over complicated this!  Potatoes roasting, then the leeks, then the fish because it cooks so fast, it all comes out at pretty much the same time then.  No hassle, no fuss.  Actually, I would probably have used a slow cooker for most of it, but not the fish.  That way, I only have to worry about the fish after work.  Everything else can be cooking while I'm busy.  SORTED used to be user friendly, now it's just for people with a ton more money and time than I have.
